The International Caries Detection and Assessment System (ICDAS) is specifically designed to accurately detect and classify carious lesions, including early, noncavitated ones—such as those in pits and fissures—which are critical for measuring the prevalence of pit and fissure caries. While DMF indexes reflect overall caries experience and cannot detect early lesions, ICDAS offers detailed staging of carious development and enables precise tracking of incipient caries, making it appropriate for evaluating the true prevalence of such lesions.

